  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "QUANTITY SURVEYOR",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Prepare cost estimates, budgets, and bills of quantities (BOQ) for construction projects.</li><li>Manage project budgets and monitor expenses to prevent cost overruns.</li><li>Conduct feasibility studies to estimate materials, time, and labor costs.</li><li>Negotiate and analyze contracts, ensuring compliance with legal and regulatory requirements.</li><li>Liaise with clients, contractors, suppliers, and consultants to ensure smooth project execution.</li><li>Measure and value the work done on-site for progress payments.</li><li>Provide advice on contractual claims and dispute resolution.</li><li>Prepare and submit tender documents and bids.</li><li>Maintain detailed project documentation and financial reports.</li><li>Monitor changes to designs, assess the impact on costs, and update budgets accordingly.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Quantity Surveying, Construction Management, Civil Engineering, or a related field.</li><li>Proven experience as a Quantity Surveyor or in a similar role.</li><li>Strong knowledge of construction methods, materials, and legal regulations.</li><li>Excellent numerical, analytical, and problem-solving skills.</li><li>Proficiency in cost-estimation software and MS Office.</li><li>Good negotiation and communication skills.</li><li>Attention to detail and strong organizational abilities.</li></ul>",
